{{onesource|date=June 2015}} {{Infobox person | honorific_prefix = | name = Hacı Sabancı | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date|1935|06|25|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Talas, Turkey|Akçakaya village]], [[Kayseri Province]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1998|06|26|1936|06|25|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Istanbul]] | death_cause = [[Lung cancer]] | resting_place = Adana Asri Cemetery | nationality = Turkish | organization = [[Sabancı Holding]] | spouse = Özcan Sabanci | children = [[Ömer Sabancı]], Demet (Sabancı) Çetindoğan, [[Mehmet Sabancı]] | parents = [[Hacı Ömer Sabancı]], Sadıka Sabancı | relatives = [[İhsan Sabancı]], [[Sakıp Sabancı]], [[Şevket Sabancı]], [[Erol Sabancı]], [[Özdemir Sabancı]]}}
'''Hacı Sabancı''' (25 June 1935 &ndash; 26 June 1998), a member of the second generation of the renowned [[Sabancı family]], was a [[Turkish people|Turkish]] businessman and [[philanthropist]].
He was born in the [[Talas, Turkey|Akçakaya village]] of [[Kayseri Province]] as the third son of [[Hacı Ömer Sabancı]], who founded Turkey's second largest industrial and financial conglomerate, [[Sabancı Holding]].
Hacı went to school and spent most of his life in [[Adana]]. After dropping out of the secondary school, he started his career in the family-owned automobile dealing and cotton exporting companies. He later served at several top management posts in different companies of Sabancı Holding. He was also president of the board of trustees of Sabancı Foundation VakSA.
==Family== He married Özcan in 1959. They had two sons, [[Ömer Sabancı|Ömer]] in 1959 and [[Mehmet Sabancı|Mehmet]] in 1963, and a daughter, Demet. [[Mehmet Sabancı|Mehmet]] died of a heart attack in 2005.{{cn|date=June 2015}}
==Death== Hacı Sabancı died on 26 June 1998, the day after his 63rd birthday, in [[İstanbul]] after a two-year struggle against [[lung cancer]]. He was laid to rest in Adana next to his murdered brother [[Özdemir Sabancı|Özdemir]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://arama.hurriyet.com.tr/arsivnews.aspx?id=-25914|newspaper=[[Hürriyet]]|title=Adanalı ‘Hacı Ağa’yı uğurladı|language=Turkish|accessdate=27 June 2015}}</ref>
