{{notability|Biographies|date=September 2015}} {{Infobox person |image = |name = Patrick Quarcoo |alias = PQ |birth_place = [[Cape Coast, Ghana|Cape Coast]], Ghana |birth_date = |occupation = Entrepreneur |years_active = 2000&ndash;present }}
'''Patrick Quarcoo''', popularly known as '''PQ''', is a Ghanaian [[Kenya]]-based [[serial entrepreneur]]. He is the founder and CEO of Radio Africa Group, which is an umbrella of among Kenya's leading media channels on print, digital, TV and radio. This include KISS 100, Classic 105, X FM, Radio Jambo, East FM, the ''Star'' newspaper and KISS TV. Quarcoo and his Radio Africa Group co-founder, William Pike also own two radio stations in [[Uganda]], Capital Radio and Beat FM. He came to Kenya from [[Reuters]] Uganda in the 90s to start up a media company.<ref>{{cite news |title=Patrick Quarcoo |url=http://positivepressagency.com/2013/02/15/interview-with-radio-africa-mogul-patrick-quarcoo |publisher=positivepressagency.com |location=Nairobi, Kenya |date=11 March 2014 |accessdate=11 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sjpaderborn.wordpress.com/2012/06/27/article-on-kenyas-top-five-media-moguls-sk-machariathe-aga-khan-patrick-quarcoo-chris-kirubi-and-uhuru-kenyatta-in-how-we-made-it-in-africa-com/|title=Article on Kenya’s top five media moguls: SK Macharia,The Aga Khan, Patrick Quarcoo, Chris Kirubi and Uhuru Kenyatta in How we made it in Africa com|work=Paderborner 'SJ' Blog|accessdate=14 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ventures-africa.com/2012/08/the-10-most-powerful-african-media-moguls/|title=Ventures Africa - The 10 Most Powerful African Media Moguls|publisher=Ventures-africa.com|accessdate=14 October 2014}}</ref> In 2012, Quarcoo was awarded an international recognition award at the [[Ghana UK-Based Achievement Awards]].
==Early life== Quarcoo was born poor in [[Cape Coast]], [[Ghana]]. He was a young journalist when he decided to put together six radio segments – reporting on what was happening in Ghana,and then sent them to the [[BBC World Service]]. Three of these segments were taken up by BBC and soon, he was reporting regularly for the BBC, [[Voice of America]], and other stations in London. {{quote |text = I think too many of us go into businesses on a wing and a prayer. I believe you can model any business. I may be wrong, but that's what I believe. Typically I start with the industry data, cut it up year by year, segment by segment, focus on the basic industry you are in. Look at what ecological and other social changes that impact that industry. Where will they take it?<ref>{{cite news |title=Patrick Quarcoo |url=http://theafricanmillionaire.blogspot.com/2013/07/patrick-quarcoo-kenyan-millionaire-how.html|publisher=theafricanmillionaire.blogspot.com |location=Nairobi, Kenya |date=11 March 2014 |accessdate=11 March 2014}}</ref>|author=Patrick Quarcoo}}
