'''Pierre Denis''' (born 21 March 1964) is the CEO of [[Jimmy Choo Ltd]], a position to which he was appointed in July 2012.<ref>http://www.cpp-luxury.com/pierre-denis-ceo-of-jimmy-choo-an-exclusive-interview/</ref>  He joined the company from [[John Galliano]],<ref>http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2012/07/23/jimmy-choo-names-pierre-denis-as-ceo</ref> where he also held the position of CEO.

Denis began his career in perfume and cosmetics and joined LVMH in 1992.<ref>http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/news-features/TMG9420697/Jimmy-Choo-name-new-CEO.html</ref>  In 1999, he was appointed Managing Director, Asia Pacific, for [[Parfums Christian Dior]]; in addition, he took over managing the [[Christian Dior S.A.|Dior Couture]] Asian business in 2004.  In 2006, Denis moved back to his native Paris to serve as Managing Director for [[Christian Dior S.A.|Christian Dior Couture]] in [[Europe]], the [[Middle East]] and [[India]].<ref>http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2178148/John-Galliano-boss-Pierre-Denis-poached-shoe-brand-Jimmy-Choo-announced-CEO.html#ixzz3DZhgjXh5</ref>  After joining [[John Galliano]] in 2008, Denis managed the business side of operations, developing the [[John Galliano]] and contemporary Galliano lines, and expanding the licensing business.  Denis is a graduate of [[ESSEC]]<ref>https://www.bloomberg.com/profiles/people/17700953-pierre-denis</ref> Paris and is based in [[Jimmy Choo Ltd|Jimmy Choo]]’s London head office.

He lives in London with his wife and three children.

